	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="month" mhs:startingPage="362"
				mhs:precedingFile="" mhs:followingFile=""
				mhs:volume="23">
				<bibl n="metadata"><date from="1821-08-01" to="1821-08-31"/></bibl>
				<!--  DJQA August 1821 vol 23 lineaday-->
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-01">
					<head>1 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-01"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<pb n="362"/>
						<dateline><hi rend="italic">August 1821.</hi></dateline>
						<p><date>1. V:</date> Wednesday. Bath— Call at <persRef ref="calhoun-john"
								>Calhoun’s</persRef> Office. <persRef ref="harris-levett"
								>Harris</persRef> papers. Draft to <persRef ref="canning-stratford"
								>Canning</persRef>. Oppressive heat.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-02">
					<head>2 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-02"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>2. V:30.</date><persRef ref="wyer-edward">Wyer</persRef> at the
							Office. Letter to <persRef key="monroe-james">P.U.S.</persRef> Evening
							at <persRef ref="hay-george">G. Hay’s</persRef>. <persRef
								ref="lee-william">W. Lee</persRef> and <persRef ref="lane-samuel"
									>Col<hi rend="superscript">l.</hi> Lane</persRef> there.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-03">
					<head>3 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-03"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>3 V:</date> Too hot for writing. Draft to <persRef ref="vives-don"
								>Vivés</persRef>— Letter to <persRef ref="walsh-robert">R.
								Walsh</persRef>— Note from <persRef key="hyde-de-neuville-jean"
								>Hyde</persRef>. Evening call at <persRef ref="frye-nathaniel"
								>Frye’s</persRef>.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-04">
					<head>4 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-04"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>4 V:15.</date> Oppressive heat. Draft to <persRef ref="vives-don"
								>Vives</persRef> finished. Despatch to <persRef ref="rush-richard"
								>R. Rush</persRef>. Letter from <persRef ref="ingersoll-joseph">J.
								R. Ingersoll</persRef>.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-05">
					<head>5 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-05"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>G 5 V:</date><persRef ref="thornton-william">D<hi
									rend="superscript">r</hi> Thornton</persRef> called, Morning and
							Evening. Heard <persRef ref="little-robert">Little</persRef>—Luke 11.4.
							Lord’s prayer. <persRef ref="bailey-john">Bailey</persRef> here.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-06">
					<head>6 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-06"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>6 V:</date><persRef ref="waggoner-unknown">M<hi rend="superscript"
									>rs. </hi>Waggoner</persRef>, <persRef ref="roberdeau-isaac"
								>Roberdeau</persRef> and <persRef ref="booker-unknown"
								>Booker</persRef>, <persRef ref="anderson-joseph">Anderson</persRef>
							and <persRef ref="thompson-smith">S. Thompson</persRef> at the Office. A
							bad Cold—</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-07">
					<head>7 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-07"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>7 V:</date><persRef key="monroe-james">P.U.S.</persRef> returned to
							the City. <persRef ref="reed-unknown2">Reed</persRef>, <persRef
								ref="mason-john">Mason</persRef>, <persRef ref="menou-charles"
								>Menou</persRef> at the Office. <persRef ref="hellen-johnson"
								>Johnson Hellen</persRef> dined out.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-08">
					<head>8 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-08"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>8 V:</date> Severe Cold. At the <persRef key="monroe-james"
								>President’s</persRef>. <persRef key="crawford-william-harris"
								>Crawford</persRef>, <persRef ref="calhoun-john">Calhoun</persRef>,
								<persRef ref="wirt-william">Wirt</persRef> there. Letter to <persRef
								ref="gallatin-albert">A. Gallatin</persRef>. Theatre opened</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-09">
					<head>9 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-09"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor><note type="subject">Slave
							Trade</note></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>9 V:30.</date> Cabinet Meeting—full. <persRef
								ref="canning-stratford">Canning</persRef> and Slave-trade. <persRef
								key="hyde-de-neuville-jean">Hyde’s</persRef> Note. <persRef
								ref="reed-unknown2">Reed</persRef><persRef ref="bowie-washington"
								>Bowie</persRef>. <persRef ref="tucker-thomas">D<hi
									rend="superscript">r</hi> Tucker</persRef>. Eve at <persRef
								ref="calhoun-john">Calhoun’s</persRef></p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-10">
					<head>10 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-10"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor><note type="subject">Slave
							Trade</note></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>10 VI:</date> Cabinet Meeting. Pension deficit— <persRef
								ref="barron-james">Barron’s</persRef> case both postponed. <persRef
								ref="canning-stratford">Canning</persRef> &amp; Slave-trade.
							Theatre.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-11">
					<head>11 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-11"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>11 V:45.</date> Cabinet Meeting— Note to <persRef
								ref="canning-stratford">Canning</persRef> resumed and adjusted—
							Draft to <persRef ref="vives-don">Vives</persRef>. Evening at the
							Play.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-12">
					<head>12 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-12"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>G 12 VI:</date><persRef ref="cook-thomas">T. Cook</persRef>, here.
							Heard <persRef ref="little-robert">Little</persRef> on Atonement late—
							Call to see <persRef ref="bailey-john">Bailey</persRef>— Caught in
							Evening Showers.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-13">
					<head>13 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-13"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>13 IV:45.</date><persRef ref="cranch-william">Judge
								Cranch</persRef> and <persRef ref="norton-richard">R. C.
								Norton</persRef> here. <persRef ref="wyer-edward">Wyer</persRef> at
							the Office— <persRef ref="roberdeau-isaac">Roberdeau</persRef>— <persRef
								ref="frye-nathaniel">Frye</persRef> here this Eve.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-14">
					<head>14 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-14"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>14 VI:</date><persRef ref="cook-thomas">T. Cook</persRef> here,
							about the house. <persRef ref="boker-unknown">Böker</persRef> at the
							Office. Letter to <persRef key="monroe-james">P.U.S.</persRef> Theatre—
								<persRef ref="thompson-smith">Thompson’s</persRef>.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-15">
					<head>15 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-15"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>15 V:30—</date> Letter from <persRef ref="jackson-andrew">Gen<hi
									rend="superscript">l.</hi> Jackson</persRef>. Pensacola
							possession. <persRef ref="gales-joseph">Gales</persRef> and <persRef
								ref="verax-unknown">Verax</persRef>. To <persRef key="monroe-james"
								>P.U.S.</persRef><persRef key="clay-henry">Clay</persRef>— Eve at
								<persRef ref="frye-nathaniel">Frye’s</persRef>.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-16">
					<head>16 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-16"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>16. V:</date><persRef ref="debresson-charles">Bresson</persRef> and
								<persRef ref="petry-jean">Petry</persRef> at the Office. Notes from
								<persRef key="hyde-de-neuville-jean">Hyde</persRef> and <persRef
								ref="stackelberg-berndt">Stackelberg</persRef>. Letter to <persRef
								key="monroe-james">P.U.S.</persRef> Play.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-17">
					<head>17 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-17"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>17 V:30.</date> Express to <persRef key="monroe-james"
								>P.U.S.</persRef><persRef ref="canning-stratford">Canning</persRef>
							at the Office. <persRef ref="stewart-unknown3">Stewart’s</persRef>
							wheat. Dined at <persRef ref="frye-nathaniel">Frye’s</persRef>. <persRef
								ref="roberdeau-isaac">Roberdeau</persRef>.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-18">
					<head>18 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-18"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>18 V:30.</date><persRef ref="lancaster-joseph">Jos.
								Lancaster</persRef> here. <persRef ref="fadin-unknown"><unclear>M
									Fadin</unclear></persRef>. At the Office. Call at <persRef
								ref="thompson-smith">S Thompson’s</persRef>. At <persRef
								ref="calhoun-john">Calhoun’s</persRef>. At the Play.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-19">
					<head>19 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-19"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>G 19 V:30.</date><persRef ref="thornton-william"
							>Thornton</persRef>. <persRef ref="hare-robert">Hare</persRef>. Heard
								<persRef ref="little-robert">Little</persRef>. <persRef
								ref="stackelberg-berndt">Stackelberg</persRef>, <persRef
								ref="roberdeau-isaac">Roberdeau</persRef>, <persRef
								ref="tone-unknown">Tone</persRef> here. At the Office. Messenger
							returned.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-20">
					<head>20 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-20"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>20 V:30.</date> Letter to <persRef key="hyde-de-neuville-jean">Hyde
								de Neuville</persRef>— He at the Office. Settlement with <persRef
								ref="vanness-john">Gen<hi rend="superscript">l.</hi> J. P. Van
								Ness</persRef>. <persRef ref="thornton-william">Thornton</persRef>
							here.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-21">
					<head>21 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-21"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>21 IV:30.</date> Stage to Baltimore. Barnum’s Steam-Boat United
							States, Trippe to French-town— Stage to</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-22">
					<head>22 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-22"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>22</date> Newcastle— St. B. Baltimore to Philadelphia—then to
							Trenton— Stage to Brunswick. Miss Sergeant</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-23">
					<head>23 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-23"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>23 V:</date> St. B. Bellona to Powles Hook—New-York—City Hotel—
							Steamship Robert Fulton for Providence</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-24">
					<head>24 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-24"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>24 V:</date> Touched at New-Haven. De Forrest, A. Bishop— Met the
							Cadets. Newport at 8. P.M. Dunham.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-25">
					<head>25 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-25"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>25 V:15.</date> Providence at 10. A.M. Stage for Boston. Dined at
							Walpole— Found my wife at Dedham. Quincy.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-26">
					<head>26 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-26"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>G 26 V:30.</date> Heard M<hi rend="superscript">r </hi>Francis of
							Watertown. W. N. Boylston’s— Degrand. Captain Beale. Quincy here.
								Sh<unclear>aws</unclear></p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-27">
					<head>27 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-27"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>27 VI:30.</date> Solar Eclipse. Shaw and Boyd to Boston. Marston
							here. Quincy, with J. S. Skinner and Pomeroy</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-28">
					<head>28 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-28"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>28 V:30.</date> John and Mary Hellen to Boston. We came in after
							dinner. At M<hi rend="superscript">rs. </hi>Jenks’s. Eve at Jos:
							Hall’s.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-29">
					<head>29 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-29"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>29 V:30.</date> Commencement day. My Son George graduated. Returned
							to Boston— Ball at H. G. Otis’s.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-30">
					<head>30 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-30"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>30 V:30.</date> Cambridge. Prize declamations. ΦBK. Oration and
							Poem. Dined at Kirkland’s. Eve M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
							Gore’s.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v23-1821-08-31">
					<head>31 August 1821</head>
					<bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1821-08-31"/><editor
							role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
					<div type="docbody">
						<p><date>31. VI:15.</date> At the Athenaeum— Received many visits. Cambridge
							with Shaw. D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Waterhouse’s. D<hi
								rend="superscript">r</hi> Welsh’s.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
